--- a/docs/examples.rst
+++ b/docs/examples.rst
@@ -244,6 +244,23 @@ Run a job until a certain time
 
 The ``until`` method sets the jobs deadline. The job will not run after the deadline.
 
+Run a job a limited number of times
+~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
+
+.. code-block:: python
+
+    import schedule
+
+    def job():
+        print('Boo')
+
+    # Run the job three times, then remove it from the scheduler.
+    schedule.every(5).seconds.max_runs(3).do(job)
+
+The ``max_runs`` method removes the job after it has executed the specified number
+of times. When combined with ``until``, the job is removed when either limit is
+reached.
+
 Time until the next execution
 ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
 Use ``schedule.idle_seconds()`` to get the number of seconds until the next job is scheduled to run.
